<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,313,1058]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,529,554]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species was first described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1902" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1902" box="[889,1296,529,554]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aleutica">
<emphasis box="[889,1125,529,553]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Pandalopsis aleutica</emphasis>
Rathbun, 1902
</taxonomicName>
(Kobjakova 1936a). Since the original description, Russian authors (e.g., Kobjakova 1936b, 1937, 1958, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinogradov, L. G." box="[1228,1428,565,590]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="179 - 358" refId="ref16896" refString="Vinogradov, L. G. (1950) Classification of shrimps, prawns and crabs from the Far East. Izvestia TINRO, 33, 179 - 358, pls. 1 - 53. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1950">Vinogradov 1950</bibRefCitation>
) repeatedly mentioned on this taxon on the basis of the original description. Hayashi (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Baba, K. &amp; Hayashi, K. &amp; Toriyama, M." box="[1127,1312,601,626]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref14392" refString="Baba, K., Hayashi, K. &amp; Toriyama, M. (1986) Decapod Crustaceans from Continental Shelf and Slope around Japan. Japan Fisheries Resource Conservation Association, Tokyo, 336 pp. [in Japanese and English]" type="book" year="1986">
Baba 
<emphasis box="[1191,1247,601,625]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
1986
</bibRefCitation>
; 2008) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Amaoka, K." box="[151,453,637,662]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="278 - 291" refId="ref16020" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Amaoka, K. (1989) Records of some rare deep-sea decapod crustaceans from the Okhotsk coast of Hokkaido (Caridea and Anomura). Bulletin of the Faculty of Fisheries, Hokkaido University, 40, 278 - 291." type="journal article" year="1989">Komai &amp; Amaoka (1989)</bibRefCitation>
reported on this species with newly collected specimens from the Sea of Okhotsk. Hayashi (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Baba, K. &amp; Hayashi, K. &amp; Toriyama, M." box="[290,478,673,698]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref14392" refString="Baba, K., Hayashi, K. &amp; Toriyama, M. (1986) Decapod Crustaceans from Continental Shelf and Slope around Japan. Japan Fisheries Resource Conservation Association, Tokyo, 336 pp. [in Japanese and English]" type="book" year="1986">
Baba 
<emphasis box="[356,413,673,697]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
1986
</bibRefCitation>
) elevated the taxon to full specific status without much justification, but subsequent authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Amaoka, K." box="[305,580,709,734]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="278 - 291" refId="ref16020" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Amaoka, K. (1989) Records of some rare deep-sea decapod crustaceans from the Okhotsk coast of Hokkaido (Caridea and Anomura). Bulletin of the Faculty of Fisheries, Hokkaido University, 40, 278 - 291." type="journal article" year="1989">Komai &amp; Amaoka 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T." box="[592,736,709,734]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="538 - 559" refId="ref15820" refString="Komai, T. (1994) Deep-sea shrimps of the genus Pandalopsis (Decapoda: Caridea: Pandalidae) from the Pacific coast of eastern Hokkaido, Japan, with the description of two new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 14, 538 - 559. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1549000" type="journal article" year="1994">Komai 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="De Grave, S. &amp; Fransen, C. H. J. M." box="[748,1047,710,734]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="195 - 589" refId="ref15060" refString="De Grave, S. &amp; Fransen, C. H. J. M. (2011) Carideorum catalogus: the recent species of the dendrobranchiate, stenopodidean, procarididean and caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda). Zoologische Mededelingen, 85, 195 - 589." type="journal article" year="2011">De Grave &amp; Fransen 2011</bibRefCitation>
) have followed his action. Indeed, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobjakova" authorityYear="1936" box="[151,257,745,769]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[151,257,745,769]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1902" box="[416,538,745,769]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aleutica">
<emphasis box="[416,538,745,769]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. aleutica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the glabrous carapace and the lack of a conspicuous lateral carina on the carapace. In the description of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Rathbun (1904)" authorityName=", Rathbun" authorityYear="1904" box="[494,801,781,806]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aleutica">
<emphasis box="[494,608,781,805]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. aleutica</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun, M. J." box="[625,801,781,806]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 210" refId="ref16670" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1904) Decapod crustaceans of the Northwest coast of North America. Harriman Alaska Expedition, 10, 1 - 210, pls. 1 - 10. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10681" type="journal article" year="1904">Rathbun (1904)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
clearly stated: “Surface of carapace covered with a short and soft pubescence. Branchial region traversed by a curved longitudinal ridge.” There is no doubt that the two taxa are specifically distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,313,1058]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
As 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T." box="[238,398,889,914]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="538 - 559" refId="ref15820" refString="Komai, T. (1994) Deep-sea shrimps of the genus Pandalopsis (Decapoda: Caridea: Pandalidae) from the Pacific coast of eastern Hokkaido, Japan, with the description of two new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 14, 538 - 559. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1549000" type="journal article" year="1994">Komai (1994)</bibRefCitation>
argued, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobjakova" authorityYear="1936" box="[497,601,889,913]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[497,601,889,913]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Komai, 1994" authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="1994" box="[658,907,889,914]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis box="[658,751,889,913]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. rubra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T." box="[760,907,889,914]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="538 - 559" refId="ref15820" refString="Komai, T. (1994) Deep-sea shrimps of the genus Pandalopsis (Decapoda: Caridea: Pandalidae) from the Pacific coast of eastern Hokkaido, Japan, with the description of two new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 14, 538 - 559. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1549000" type="journal article" year="1994">Komai, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar for one another, but the latter species seems to occur at greater depths than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobjakova" authorityYear="1936" box="[676,781,925,949]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[676,781,925,949]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T." box="[837,982,925,950]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="538 - 559" refId="ref15820" refString="Komai, T. (1994) Deep-sea shrimps of the genus Pandalopsis (Decapoda: Caridea: Pandalidae) from the Pacific coast of eastern Hokkaido, Japan, with the description of two new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 14, 538 - 559. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1549000" type="journal article" year="1994">Komai 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 2008; 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Komatsu, H." box="[1068,1354,925,950]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="495 - 580" refId="ref16122" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Komatsu, H. (2009) Deep-Sea shrimps and lobsters (Crustacea: Decapoda: Penaeidea, Caridea, Polychelidea) from northern Japan, collected during the Project &quot; Research on Deep-sea Fauna and Pollutants off Pacific Coast of Northern Honshu, Japan, 2005 - 2008. &quot; National Museum of Nature and Science Monographs, 39, 495 - 580." type="journal article" year="2009">Komai &amp; Komatsu 2009</bibRefCitation>
; Marin 2018). The record by Birshtein &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarenkov, N. A." box="[535,718,961,986]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="176 - 194" refId="ref17196" refString="Zarenkov, N. A. (1971) Contribution to the study of the species and of the geographic distribution of the marine shrimps belonging to the families Hippolytidae and Pandalidae (Crustacea, Decapoda). Kompleksnve Issledovaniia Prirodi Okeana Moskovskogo Universiteta, 2, 176 - 194." type="journal article" year="1971">Zarenkov (1971</bibRefCitation>
; as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobjakova" authorityYear="1936" box="[760,961,961,985]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="aleutica" subSpecies="glabra">
<emphasis box="[760,961,961,985]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. aleutica glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
