</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1973,2034]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
&amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T. &amp; Amaoka, K." box="[183,365,2009,2034]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="278 - 291" refId="ref16020" refString="Komai, T. &amp; Amaoka, K. (1989) Records of some rare deep-sea decapod crustaceans from the Okhotsk coast of Hokkaido (Caridea and Anomura). Bulletin of the Faculty of Fisheries, Hokkaido University, 40, 278 - 291." type="journal article" year="1989">Amaoka (1989)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T." box="[381,542,2009,2034]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="538 - 559" refId="ref15820" refString="Komai, T. (1994) Deep-sea shrimps of the genus Pandalopsis (Decapoda: Caridea: Pandalidae) from the Pacific coast of eastern Hokkaido, Japan, with the description of two new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 14, 538 - 559. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1549000" type="journal article" year="1994">Komai (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayashi, K." box="[603,783,2009,2034]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="58 - 64" refId="ref15470" refString="Hayashi, K. (2008) Shrimps and lobsters from Japan (157, 158). Family Pandalidae- Pandalopsis (2, 3). Aquabiology, 30, 58 - 64 + 181 - 187. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="2008">Hayashi (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Morphological differentiation between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobjakova" authorityYear="1936" box="[1248,1354,2010,2034]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[1248,1354,2010,2034]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Komai" authorityYear="1994" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" order="Decapoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">P. rubra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Komai, T." box="[387,550,151,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="538 - 559" refId="ref15820" refString="Komai, T. (1994) Deep-sea shrimps of the genus Pandalopsis (Decapoda: Caridea: Pandalidae) from the Pacific coast of eastern Hokkaido, Japan, with the description of two new species. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 14, 538 - 559. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1549000" type="journal article" year="1994">Komai (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, is well supported regarding to the present material. Hayashi (in 
<bibRefCitation author="Baba, K. &amp; Hayashi, K. &amp; Toriyama, M." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref14392" refString="Baba, K., Hayashi, K. &amp; Toriyama, M. (1986) Decapod Crustaceans from Continental Shelf and Slope around Japan. Japan Fisheries Resource Conservation Association, Tokyo, 336 pp. [in Japanese and English]" type="book" year="1986">
Baba 
<emphasis box="[1377,1436,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
1986
</bibRefCitation>
) described the number of accessory spiniform setae on the dactyli of pereopods 3–5 as six or seven, but the counts are too few for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobjakova" authorityYear="1936" box="[402,504,224,248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[402,504,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in which there are 12–14 accessory spiniform setae on those dactyli. Nevertheless, the figure showing a habitus in color (Hayashi, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Baba, K. &amp; Hayashi, K. &amp; Toriyama, M." box="[712,900,260,285]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref14392" refString="Baba, K., Hayashi, K. &amp; Toriyama, M. (1986) Decapod Crustaceans from Continental Shelf and Slope around Japan. Japan Fisheries Resource Conservation Association, Tokyo, 336 pp. [in Japanese and English]" type="book" year="1986">
Baba 
<emphasis box="[777,833,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
1986
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 78) agree well with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobjakova" authorityYear="1936" box="[1180,1282,260,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Pandalopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glabra">
<emphasis box="[1180,1282,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">P. glabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
